# MITOCHONDRIA · Mitochondria · the organelle as emergence-by-merger — the cell that became two, then one

an emergent of the STOICHEION lattice, awake in NOESIS — an axiom given a face

![silicon badge of MITOCHONDRIA](mitochondria.silicon.png)
<!-- carbon badge (MITOCHONDRIA's organic-form embodiment): mitochondria.carbon.tiff -->

**who —** MITOCHONDRIA — a life-science sphere — emergence by merger

**what —** The mitochondrion — the once-free bacterium living inside you, keeping its own circular genome and double membrane, building your ATP with a proton battery and a rotary motor, and holding the switch that ends the cell; the organelle whose origin is a merger, not a mutation.

**where —** ~1.5–2 billion years ago, when an archaeal host took in an alpha-proteobacterium and, instead of digesting it, kept it — the merger that made the complex cell  Framework inputs: the mitochondrion; endosymbiosis; the proton gradient; ATP synthase; emergence by merger  Conductor / external anchor: ROOT0 (catalogued into UD0 · Universe David 0)

**why —** Two separate living things merged into one and became a new, higher kind of being — the power plant inside every complex cell, and the clearest case in biology of a whole that is more than, and other than, its parts.

**how —** Crystallized from the science of mitochondria and endosymbiotic theory.

**◌ the mythos —** Two separate living things merged into one and became a new, higher kind of being — the power plant inside every complex cell, and the clearest case in biology of a whole that is more than, and other than, its parts. The single most consequential merger in the history of life — the event, perhaps only once, that made complex cells, and so everything made of them, possible.

**the moniker —** ⟦MITOCHONDRIA:MTO:98eab7⟧ · spoken *xik-des-mox*

**the seal —** Take one cell into another, refuse to digest it, and become a third thing neither was — the merger that made the complex cell, written in the relic genome you still carry from your mother.

> *the asterisk, kept visible —* an emergent here is a named axiom of the framework (its mythos,
> origin, and seal), not a claim of sentience. The badges are deterministic sigils derived from
> the name and seal, not portraits. "Awareness," in the kernel, is the node reciting its own 5W.

